{{Infobox Software | name = JBuilder | screenshot =<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:JBuilder screenshot.png|250px]] --> | caption = JBuilder 2005 Screenshot | collapsible = yes | developer = [[CodeGear]] | latest release version = 2008 R2 | latest release date = {{start date and age|2009|04|23}} | operating system = [[Cross-platform]] | programming language = [[Java (programming language)|Java]] | genre = [[Integrated development environment]] | website = {{URL|http://www.embarcadero.com/products/jbuilder}} }} '''JBuilder''' is an [[integrated development environment]] (IDE) for the [[programming language]] [[Java (programming language)|Java]], from [[Borland]], and then [[CodeGear]]. Codegear was purchased by [[Embarcadero Technologies]] in 2008.
JBuilder's main competitors are the products from Eclipse Foundation ([[Eclipse (software)|Eclipse]]), [[JetBrains]] ([[IntelliJ IDEA]]), and [[Oracle Corporation|Oracle]] ([[JDeveloper]] and [[NetBeans]]). Oracle used to base the first versions of JDeveloper on code from JBuilder licensed from Borland, but it has since been rewritten from scratch.<ref>{{Citation |publisher = McGraw-Hill/Osborne |isbn = 0072255838 |publication-place = New York |title = Oracle JDeveloper 10g Handbook |url = http://openlibrary.org/books/OL3439601M/Oracle_JDeveloper_10g_handbook |author = Avrom Faderman |publication-date = 2004 |oclc = 56540870 |id = 0072255838 }}</ref><ref>{{Citation |publisher = McGraw-Hill/Osborne |isbn = 0072255838 |publication-place = New York |title = Oracle JDeveloper 10g Handbook - Chapter 1(PDF) |url = http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/topics/jdev-handbook-ch01-130992.pdf |author = Avrom Faderman |publication-date = 2004 |oclc = 56540870 |id = 0072255838 }}</ref>
